Result: false  
Justification:  
The condition C11 requires that for every minimal semantic basis of the claim, there exists at least one P-type argument whose justification contains that basis. The claim is "Dr. Atharv contributes to agriculture." The minimal semantic basis for this claim is that Dr. Atharv studies autogamy (since from the given information, studying autogamy leads to contributing to agriculture). However, among the P-type arguments, none have a justification that directly states or logically guarantees that Dr. Atharv actually studies autogamy—they only state that he *can* study autogamy (possibility) or that *if* he studies autogamy, then he contributes. Since the necessary condition (actually studying autogamy) is not established in any P-type argument's justification, C11 is not satisfied.